stationary unless cast on a mobile object. The spell can be
centered on a creature, and the effect then radiates from the
creature and moves as it moves. An unwilling creature can attempt
a Will save to negate the spell and can use SR, if any. Items in
a creature's possession or magic items that emit sound
receive saves and SR, and unattended objects and points in space
do not.
